EDSS scores 0.0-3.5 and 4.0-6.0 than for scores > 6.0 (P < 0.05). The 
extrapolated data gave an estimated annual direct cost of MS per patient of 
<euro>18,030. In conclusion, relapsing-remitting MS or secondary progressive MS 
phenotypes and lower estimated EDSS scores appear to be associated with higher 
costs.

