BACKGROUND/AIMS: The japanese population have the longest-life expectancy in the 
world. Accordingly, older patients with colorectal cancer with senile kyphosis 
caused by aging or osteoporosis also increase. Laparoscopic surgery is 
minimally-invasive, and performance on severe kyphotic patients may cause 
difficulty to approach a narrow abdomen. To determine whether laparoscopic 
surgery is safe and feasible in patients with severe senile kyphosis.
